// Kodex Layout
// Shell component for all Kodex pages. Provides a full-width top header with connection status,
// project selector, refresh control, and theme toggle, a left sidebar below the header,
// and a main content area for child routes.
// synced: 2026-03-26T14:00:05Z

FUNCTION KodexLayout()                                                  EXPORT  [2026-03-26]
  CALLS: fetchProjects (kodexStore), setSelectedProject (kodexStore)
  On mount: call fetchProjects to load the registered project list.
  If no project is selected and a collab session is active, auto-select the session's project.
  Apply dark/light theme class to the document root whenever theme changes.

  handleRefreshProjects: call fetchProjects.

  handleAddProject: prompt the user for a path. POST to /api/projects to register it.
    On success: refresh projects and select the new path.

  Render:
    - Full-width top header (h-12) with: "Kodex" route name label, connection status
      badge (green/yellow/red), refresh button, ProjectSelector, and theme toggle button.
    - Body row below the header: KodexSidebar on the left, main content area (Outlet) on the right.
